Jan Luca Schuler (born 22 March 1999) is a German footballer who plays as a forward for 1. FC Magdeburg.


== Career ==
Schuler began playing football at the age of 3 with Niederkirchen, and continued his development at the youth academies of Meckenheim, 1. FC Kaiserslautern, SV Elversberg, and 1. FC Saarbrücken. He signed his first professional contract with 1. FC Köln II in March 2018.Schuler made his professional debut for Schalke 04 in the Bundesliga on 28 November 2020, coming on as a substitute in the 81st minute for Matthew Hoppe against Borussia Mönchengladbach. The away match finished as a 4–1 loss.


